      "page_number": 20,
      "section": "act_three",
      "speaker": "clive",
      "speaker_mode": "dialogue",
      "text": "Neither do I. Yet. But I've been around long enough to know when something's remembering itself. He looked at me. Pixel asked what the Keeper showed us. What I saw was them—the Keepers, when they were alive and whole—and something else. Something built to carry their memories. Something that could move. Could preserve. Could continue.",
